Body:
Description: Hello, 

We currently have a public folder report setup for our Exchange On-Prem environment, but we have recently migrated our public folders to exchange online. We'd like some guidance on how to repoint this folder to point to EXO instead of Exchange On-Prem. Thanks
Steps to Reproduce Updated: Looking to create a report that pulls data from Exchange online for the Publics folder
What We've Learned Updated: Customer is looking to re-create a report for their Exchange Online version of their public folder
This is a Netwrix Enterprise Auditor case, updating product in the case details and reassigning as I do not support NEA
Invitation updated. Attendees: No attendees listed
Invitation updated. Attendees: Scottie Taylor, Lenny Jones
Invitation updated. Attendees: Scottie Taylor, Tay Caliguiri
Invitation updated. Attendees: Scottie Taylor, Tay Caliguiri, Lenny Jones

Next Steps Updated: Our next steps are:

You will:

Check dependencies and permissions and attempt to run the job once more

What We've Learned Updated: Customer is looking to re-create a report for their Exchange Online version of their public folder


Today we:

Reviewed the configurations for the EXO Public Report detailed in the documentation below:

https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/EnterpriseAuditor_11.6/page/Content/EnterpriseAuditor/Solutions/Exchange/PublicFolders/Recommended.htm

Recommended verifying that the dependencies listed in the document above are installed on the NEA application server. 

Verified that the ADI and Entra ID jobs successfully ran.

Verified the host list is set to localhost. 

Recommend checking the MAPI-Based Permissions as well. 

https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/EnterpriseAuditor_11.6/page/Content/EnterpriseAuditor/Requirements/Solutions/Exchange/MAPI.htm

This didnt have to do with dependencies. They already had EXO scans running just not on Public folders as all their public folders were on EX On Prem. We moved the Public Folders group to Exchange Online and ran the jobs. Problem solved as they dont have any more public folders in On Prem.
Customer would like the case closed. You can say that I chatted with you. Happy to go over what I did in a lab with you if you like.
